2011-05-30T20:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-30/group-polymetal-rosneft-sberbank-russian-equity-preview-by.html
The following companies may be active
in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and share
prices are from the previous close of trading in Moscow.  The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  advanced 0.4 percent to 1,644.99
by the close in Moscow. The dollar-denominated RTS Index added
0.4 percent to 1,865.74.  OAO Dixy Group (DIXY RX): The Russian supermarket chain
fell 0.5 percent to 384 rubles. The company plans to spend 664
million rubles ($23 million) on changing the format of its
retail network, President Ilya Yakubson said in a video-
conference yesterday from  London .  OAO Polymetal (PMTL RX): The Russian silver and gold
producer gained for a third day, adding 3.9 percent to 527.8
rubles. Silver for July delivery jumped as much as 1.4 percent
to $38.395 an ounce, extending last week’s 7.9 percent gain.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX):  Russia ’s biggest oil producer
rallied 0.3 percent to 241.68 rubles. Oil futures slipped as
much as 1 percent in  New York  on speculation that fuel demand
will falter amid a slowdown in the U.S. economic recovery and
 Europe ’s continuing debt crisis.  OAO Sberbank (SBER03 RX): Russia’s biggest lender is
scheduled to release its first-quarter earnings. Its stock
gained for the fifth day, adding 0.4 percent to 97.32 rubles. 